wikipedia_page.main: Andre Tjay De Barr (born 13 March 2000) is a Gibraltarian footballer who plays for League One side Wycombe Wanderers, and the Gibraltar national football team, as a forward. He is currently the joint-record scorer for his national team, with three goals.

response: He spent most of his career with lower-league Spanish clubs and in the Gibraltar Premier Division. He also had brief spells with England's Portsmouth (League One) and Notts County (League Two), and Bnei Yehuda Tel Aviv in the Israeli Premier League. He made his international debut for Gibraltar in their first official game in 2013, and as of 2021, he is the joint-record caps holder for Gibraltar (held with Roy Chipolina) and joint-record goalscorer (alongside Lee Casciaro, Tjay De Barr and Reece Styche).

Reece Styche (born 3 May 1989) is a professional footballer who plays as a striker for Southern League Premier Division club Stourbridge and the Gibraltar national team. Known as a physical attacker, he is also known as "Brutus" by fans in Gibraltar after the nickname was given to him by head coach Julio Cesar Ribas.Non-league striker reflects on 'amazing' World Cup qualifying experience Yahoo! Finance. 9 April 2021. Retrieved 21 April 2021. He currently holds the record of joint-highest scorer for Gibraltar, shared with Tjay De Barr, Liam Walker and Lee Casciaro.

Defender Roy Chipolina and midfielder Liam Walker are the nation's most capped players, accumulating 57 appearances since their international debuts in November 2013 against Slovakia. Forwards Lee Casciaro, Tjay De Barr, Reece Styche and Liam Walker are the nation's leading goalscorers of all time, scoring three in 43, 28, 21 and 57 matches respectively. Kyle Goldwin is the most capped goalkeeper in Gibraltar's history having appeared 21 times for the national side. Defender Joseph Chipolina has received the most yellow cards (cautions), with ten. Defender Jayce Olivero has received the most red cards (dismissals), with two sending off. Since their official debut in 2013, 63 players have made at least one international appearance for Gibraltar.

Ethan Terence Jolley (born 29 March 1997) is a Gibraltarian footballer who plays as a defender for Europa and the Gibraltar national team. He is the cousin of fellow national team footballer Tjay De Barr.

Jolley made his international debut for Gibraltar on 26 March 2019, coming on as a substitute for Tjay De Barr in second-half stoppage time of the friendly match against Estonia, which finished as a 0–1 home loss.
